claim.claim-text:
An intake air supply structure for a turbo supercharger (1) comprising:
an exhaust side impeller (22) of a turbine rotated by exhaust gas discharged from an internal combustion engine;
an intake side impeller (21) of a compressor connected to the exhaust side impeller (22), the intake side impeller (21) configured to rotate to force-feed intake air toward the internal combustion engine;
an intake flow path (11) configured to guide the intake air to the intake side impeller (21); and
an intake air swirling means (50; 50A; 50B; 50C) provided on an outer periphery of the intake flow path (11), the intake air swirling means (50; 50A; 50B; 50C) configured to extract a portion of the intake air inside the intake flow path (11) temporarily to an exterior of the intake flow path (11), and to swirl the extracted intake air in the same direction as a rotational direction of the intake side impeller (21) along the outer periphery of the intake flow path (11), and to discharge the swirled intake air into the intake flow path (11).
